    <abstract>
      <p>Genome Surveyor 2.0 is a web-based tool for discovery and analysis of <italic>cis-</italic>regulatory elements in <italic>Drosophila</italic>, built on top of the GBrowse genome browser for convenient visualization. Genome Surveyor was developed as a tool for predicting transcription factor (TF) binding targets and <italic>cis-</italic>regulatory modules (CRMs/enhancers), based on motifs representing experimentally determined DNA binding specificities. Since its first publication, we have added substantial new functionality (e.g. phylogenetic averaging of motif scores from multiple species, and a novel CRM discovery technique), increased the number of supported motifs about 4-fold (from ∼100 to ∼400), added provisions for evolutionary comparison across many more <italic>Drosophila</italic> species (from 2 to 12), and improved the user-interface. The server is free and open to all users, and there is no login requirement. Address: <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://veda.cs.uiuc.edu/gs">http://veda.cs.uiuc.edu/gs</ext-link>.</p>
    </abstract>
